0walking%20around%20with%20engorged%20breasts%20that%20felt%20like%20rocks%20on%20my%20chest%20as%20I%20struggled%20with%20breastfeeding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20daughter%2C%20who%20is%20now%2015%2C%20was%20born%20when%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20were%20starting%20a%20company%20that%20distributed%20Korean%20television%20shows%20to%20the%20US%20market.%20Since%20it%20was%20a%20startup%2C%20I%20didn't%20have%20the%20luxury%20of%20a%20day%20off%2C%20and%20I%20returned%20to%20work%20immediately%20after%20she%20was%20born.%20I%20remember%20her%20crying%20while%20I%20was%20working%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0and%20being%20so%20angry%2C%20thinking%2C%C2%A0%26quot%3BWhy%20is%20that%20baby%20distracting%20me%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%20I%20wasn't%20able%20to%20celebrate%20my%20new%20life%20as%20a%20mom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20son%2C%20who%20is%20now%2011%2C%20had%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fc-section-things-i-wished-i-knew-before-birth-2021-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EC-section%20birth%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20physical%20recovery%20was%20very%20challenging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22958bd0a3-fb3a-4b12-81b8-a64b074f51fa%5C%22%3EMy%20friends%20in%20Korea%20had%20very%20different%20experiences%20from%20mine%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20born%20in%20the%20US%20while%20my%20parents%20were%20studying%20here%2C%20but%20I%20was%20raised%20in%20Korea.%20My%20kids%20were%20both%20born%20in%20New%20York%2C%20and%20we%20identify%20as%20Korean-American.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%20the%20time%20my%20son%20was%20born%2C%20my%20friends%20in%20Korea%20were%20having%20their%20first%20babies.%20Their%20experiences%20were%20so%20different%20from%20mine.%20Korea%2C%20like%20New%20York%2C%20has%20a%20fast-paced%20hustle%20culture.%20But%20there's%20a%20Korean%20saying%20that%20after%20giving%20birth%20is%20a%20time%20to%20walk%20slowly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoms%20go%20from%20the%20hospital%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoms-new-boram-postpartum-retreat-babies-new-york-2022-06%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epostpartum%20retreats%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20they%20usually%20stay%20for%20two%20weeks.%20There%20are%20different%20levels%20of%20retreats%2C%20including%20some%20run%20by%20the%20government%2C%20and%2084%25%20of%20Korean%20moms%20go%20to%20one.%20They%20get%20three%20meals%20a%20day%2C%20lactation%20support%2C%20and%20childcare%2C%20which%20gives%20them%20the%20time%20to%20rest%20and%20recover.%20When%20they%20go%20home%2C%20they%20have%20structured%20support%20of%20home%20visits%20for%20the%20first%20six%20months%20postpartum.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20friends%20who%20had%20that%20support%20were%20thriving.%20They%20were%20able%20to%20ease%20into%20their%20new%20role%20as%20moms.%20Meanwhile%2C%20I%20was%20in%20the%20US%20without%20my%20village%2C%20feeling%20constantly%20cold%20and%20trying%20to%20heal%20my%20incision.%20My%20son%20vomited%20after%20each%20feed%2C%20so%20I%20had%20a%20designated%20puke%20shirt%20that%20just%20perpetually%20smelled%20like%20milky%20vomit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2234bb4912-1776-44c1-97dd-bd4fcf877631%5C%22%3EWe%20started%20a%20retreat%2C%20but%20found%20home%20care%20was%20a%20better%20fit%20here%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20me%20about%20two%20years%20to%20start%20feeling%20better%20after%20my%20son's%20birth.%20My%20husband%20and%20I%20had%20sold%20our%20streaming%20business%2C%20but%20wanted%20to%20stay%20entrepreneurs.%20We%20saw%20an%20opportunity%20to%20mimic%20the%20Korean%20model%2C%20providing%20postpartum%20support%20to%20new%20moms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-mom-sparks-debate-with-korean-postpartum-care-center-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eopened%20Boram%20Care%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202022.%20We%20leased%20space%20in%20a%20New%20York%20hotel%20and%20provided%20moms%20with%20food%2C%20lactation%20support%2C%20postpartum%20doulas%2C%20and%20nannies%2024%2F7.%20Some%20moms%20stayed%20for%20three%20nights%2C%20while%20others%20stayed%20longer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20loved%20seeing%20the%20benefits%20for%20women%2C%20but%20there%20are%20so%20many%20cultural%20differences%20between%20the%20US%20and%20Korea.%20In%20Korea%2C%20postpartum%20retreats%20are%20normal%20and%20accepted%20%E2%80%94%20in%20fact%2C%20booking%20a%20retreat%20is%20one%20of%20the%20first%20things%20women%20do%20when%20they%20find%20out%20they're%20expecting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20doesn't%20have%20a%20widespread%20understanding%20of%20retreats.%20However%2C%20we're%20already%20familiar%20with%20home%20care%20for%20older%20people%20or%20small%20children%20via%20nannies.%20To%20better%20fit%20our%20American%20demographic%2C%20Boram%20Care%20pivoted%20to%20provide%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-am-a-doula-this-is-what-i-do-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epostpartum%20doulas%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20lactation%20support%2C%20and%20childcare%20in%20people's%20homes.%20I%20hope%20that%20eventually%2C%20this%20can%20lead%20to%20more%20accessible%20and%20affordable%20postpartum%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221075af15-be07-4631-8470-a5cd22c79350%5C%22%3EI%20want%20to%20help%20women%20celebrate%20their%20postpartum%20experience%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Korean%2C%20Boram%20means%20%26quot%3Bthe%20fruits%20of%20one's%20labor.%26quot%3B%20It's%20my%20name%2C%20of%20course%2C%20but%20it%20was%20also%20the%20perfect%20name%20for%20a%20business%20meant%20to%20help%20mothers%20enjoy%20and%20celebrate%20the%20fruits%20of%20their%20labor%20%E2%80%94%20their%20precious%20babies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-gave-birth-in-netherlands-postpartum-support-life-changing-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPostpartum%20support%3C%2Fa%3E%20isn't%20a%20luxury%3B%20it's%20essential.%20Korean%20society%20understands%20that%2C%20and%20I%20hope%20that%20with%20time%2C%20the%20US%20will%20enact%20policies%20that%20