ection%20that%20he's%20partial%20to%20'70s%20funk%20and%20classical%20jazz%20and%20that%20his%20son%20%26quot%3Bhas%20gotten%20me%20into%20country.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20jury%20now%20has%20four%20Black%20jurors%20instead%20of%20the%20originally%20chosen%20five.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20removed%20juror%20told%20the%20judge%20during%20voir%20dire%20that%20he%20lived%20in%20the%20Bronx%20with%20his%20girlfriend%20and%20their%20daughter.%20During%20the%20trial%2C%20however%2C%20he%20made%20an%20offhand%20remark%20to%20a%20court%20employee%20that%20he'd%20moved%20to%20New%20Jersey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20employee%20brought%20this%20information%20to%20Subramanian's%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20at%20least%20two%20behind-closed-door%20sessions%20last%20week%2C%20the%20former%20juror%20No.%206%20was%20asked%20to%20clarify%20where%20he%20lived.%20He%20continued%20to%20give%20inconsistent%20answers%20while%20under%20questioning%20by%20the%20judge%20in%20front%20of%20the%20parties%20and%20outside%20the%20presence%20of%20other%20jurors%20or%20the%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20dismissed%20juror%20was%20removed%20despite%20repeated%20objections%20from%20Combs'%20defense%20lawyers%2C%20who%20argued%20that%20it%20was%20racist%20to%20remove%20a%20Black%20juror%20and%20replace%20him%20with%20a%20white%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECombs'%20lawyer%2C%20Xavier%20Donaldson%2C%20had%20asked%20Friday%20that%20the%20judge%20bring%20in%20juror%20No.%206%20to%20clarify%20his%20inconsistencies%20once%20again%2C%20but%20the%20judge%20declined%2C%20saying%20he%20had%20already%20been%20questioned%20about%20it%20twice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20that%20is%20of%20paramount%20importance%2C%20sometimes%20above%20just%20about%20all%20else%2C%20that%20we%20have%20a%20jury%20that%20is%20representative%20of%20who%20they're%20making%20decisions%20against%2C%20particularly%20in%20this%20city%2C%26quot%3B%20Donaldson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20the%20parties%20said%20that%20